<p><strong>Revenue model:</strong> Free (offline journal, zero hosting cost), $2/mo (sync + MCP access), $5/mo (cloud transcription), $10/mo (AI reflections, vector search, synthesis). COGS are low — transcription and embeddings cost a fraction of heavy AI inference.</p>
<p><strong>Funding to date:</strong> $0. The entire product has been built by the founder with no outside funding.</p>

<h2>Investment</h2>
<p>Raising <strong>$300,000</strong> via SAFE note (YC standard) at a <strong>$5M valuation cap</strong>. Deliberately priced as early-believer terms — TwinMind raised at $60M with 30K users; we are raising pre-launch.</p>
<p><strong>Use of funds:</strong> Bring core team (founder + two co-leads) full-time through 2026, fund infrastructure, and execute production launch by June 2026. Goal is revenue on launch with sufficient growth to raise a subsequent round by early 2027.</p>
<p><strong>NVC prize funds ($50,000)</strong> would accelerate team ramp-up, broader beta distribution, and an earlier path to growth metrics for the next raise.</p>

